WORKOUT_TRACKER_FORMAT_VERSION=1.0

OUTPUT_RULES:
1) Output exactly one JSON object.
2) No markdown, no code fences, no extra text.
3) Must be valid parseable JSON.
4) Do not include properties outside schema.

TOP_LEVEL_SCHEMA:
{
  "version": "1.0",
  "program_name": "string",
  "description": "string (optional)",
  "workouts": [WorkoutDay]
}

WORKOUT_DAY_SCHEMA:
{
  "day_of_week": "Monday|Tuesday|Wednesday|Thursday|Friday|Saturday|Sunday",
  "week_offset": "integer >= 0 (optional)",
  "name": "string",
  "exercises": [Exercise]
}

EXERCISE_SCHEMA:
{
  "id": "lowercase-kebab-case string",
  "name": "string",
  "muscle_group": "string (optional)",
  "sets": "integer >= 1",
  "target_reps": "string, e.g. 5 or 8-12",
  "starting_weight_kg": "number >= 0 (optional)",
  "starting_reps": "integer >= 1 (optional)",
  "rest_seconds": "integer >= 1 (optional)",
  "reference_url": "valid URL string (optional)",
  "notes": "string (optional)"
}

SCHEDULING_RULES:
- Weekly plans should omit week_offset.
- Alternating plans can use week_offset values, e.g. 0 and 1.

QUALITY_RULES:
- Use realistic exercises, sets, reps, and rest times.
- Include 3-6 exercises per workout day unless user asks otherwise.
- Exercise ids should be unique within the plan.

REFERENCE_FILES:
- https://fitness.abhishekdoesstuff.com/format/schema.json
- https://fitness.abhishekdoesstuff.com/format/example.json
